--- PART 3: DETAILED TRANSITION ANALYSIS ---
Copart > 0 iff (chi(q)=+1, chi(q+1)=-1) or (chi(q)=-1, chi(q-1)=+1)
First condition = Type A transition at ODD q
Second condition = Type B transition at ODD q (since chi(q-1)=+1, chi(q)=-1)
NO! Second is: chi(q)=-1 and chi(q-1)=+1, i.e., Type A at EVEN n=q-1

  p=7:
    q= 3: chi(q)=-1, chi(q-1)=+1 -> copart=Y [A-type at q-1]
    q= 5: chi(q)=-1, chi(q-1)=+1 -> copart=Y [A-type at q-1]
    Total: 0 from A-at-odd + 2 from A-at-even = 2

  p=11:
    q= 3: chi(q)=+1, chi(q+1)=+1 -> copart=N [C-type at q]
