--- PART 7: SIGN LAW CONNECTION ---
The sign formula from resonance cascade:
  sign(D^{2n}_onset) * chi(ab) = chi(q)

For the product law sign(h_hat) = chi(ab):
  Need sign(h_hat) = chi(ab)
  If h_hat dominated by D^{2n}_onset:
    sign(h_hat) = sign(D^{2n}_onset) = chi(q)*chi(ab)
    Product law requires chi(q)=+1

At p=3 mod 4 with chi(q)=-1 (e.g., q=3 at p=19):
  Dominant D^4 has wrong sign
  ALSO: copart(q=3) depends on chi(8)=chi(2)^3

  p=7: chi(2)=+1, chi(3)=-1
    q=3: chi(3)=-1, chi(2)=+1, copart=Y
    q=5: chi(5)=-1, chi(4)=+1, copart=Y
    Sign law OK for q=3? chi(3)==-1 NO (D^4 wrong sign)

  p=11: chi(2)=-1, chi(3)=+1
    q=3: chi(3)=+1, chi(4)=+1, copart=N
    q=5: chi(5)=+1, chi(6)=-1, copart=Y
    Sign law OK for q=3? chi(3)==+1 YES

  p=19: chi(2)=-1, chi(3)=-1
    q=3: chi(3)=-1, chi(2)=-1, copart=N
    q=5: chi(5)=+1, chi(6)=+1, copart=N
    Sign law OK for q=3? chi(3)==-1 NO (D^4 wrong sign)

  p=23: chi(2)=+1, chi(3)=+1
    q=3: chi(3)=+1, chi(4)=+1, copart=N
    q=5: chi(5)=-1, chi(4)=+1, copart=Y
    Sign law OK for q=3? chi(3)==+1 YES

  p=31: chi(2)=+1, chi(3)=-1
