    q=5: chi(5)=-1, chi(4)=+1, copart=Y
    Sign law OK for q=3? chi(3)==-1 NO (D^4 wrong sign)


--- PART 8: ASYMPTOTIC COPART FRACTION ---
Heuristically, chi(q) and chi(q+/-1) are 'independent' for large p.
Then P(copart=Y) = P(chi(q)=+1)*P(chi(q+1)=-1) + P(chi(q)=-1)*P(chi(q-1)=+1)
                  = (1/2)(1/2) + (1/2)(1/2) = 1/2

